HEADWORD: Theanthropism
<hw>The*an"thro*pism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ god
+ <?/ man.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A state of being God and man.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Coleridge.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The ascription of human atributes to the Deity, or
to a polytheistic deity; anthropomorphism.</def>
<rj><au>Gladstone.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Theanthropist</ent>⟦br⟧
